com.pb.sawdust.tabledata

Class AbstractTableKey<K>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.pb.sawdust.tabledata.AbstractTableKey<K>
  • Type Parameters:
    K - The type of the table key.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    TableIndex<K>, TableKey<K>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    BasicTableKey, FrozenTableKey

    public abstract class AbstractTableKey<K>
extends java.lang.Object
implements TableKey<K>

    The AbstractTableKey class provides a skeletal version of TableKey which reduces the coding burden on the implementing user. It actually implements all of the methods from TableKey, leaving it to the implementing class to form the key lookup table.

    • Method Detail

      • getKeyIndex

        protected abstract InjectiveMap<K,java.lang.Integer> getKeyIndex()
        Build a lookup table used to map key values to table data rows. This key index should be constructed such that getRowNumber(key) is identical to getKeyIndex().get(key). This method should account for changes made to the underlying/referring data table. That is, if a data table is altered in some manner, then subsequent calls to this method will reflect these changes. This mapping should be unique, so that no map value (row number) is repeated (matched to more than one key). The map's value set should form a complete set of all row numbers in the underlying/referring data table.
        Returns:
        the mapping from key values to row numbers.

      • getRowNumbers

        public java.util.Set<java.lang.Integer> getRowNumbers(K... indexValues)
        Description copied from interface: TableIndex
        Get the row numbers corresponding to a given set of index values. The index column values must be provided in the same order as returned by TableIndex.getIndexColumnLabels(). If no rows are found corresponding to the index values, an exception is thrown (as opposed to returning an empty set, which could mask errors). The row numbers returned will correspond to the order of the source data table when the index was last built.
